Docs.summary: Represents a method or method-like symbol (including constructor, destructor, operator, or property/event accessor).
Docs.remarks: This interface is reserved for implementation by its associated APIs. We reserve the right to change it in the future.

Note, the set of possible associated symbols might be expanded in the future to reflect changes in the languages.

MemberSignature.Value: public: property bool IsVararg { bool get(); };
Public ReadOnly Property IsVararg As Boolean

Docs.summary:
Returns whether this method is using CLI VARARG calling convention. This is used for C-style variable argument lists. This is used extremely rarely in C# code and is represented using the undocumented "__arglist" keyword.
Note that methods with "params" on the last parameter are indicated with the "IsParams" property on ParameterSymbol, and are not represented with this property.
